<div class="section-label">Section 08</div>
<div class="section-title hidden stagger-1">Artists &amp; Pioneers</div>
<div class="section-sub hidden stagger-2">The innovators who turned effects into expression</div>
<div class="artists-grid">
<div class="artist-card hidden stagger-1">
<div class="artist-name">Jimi Hendrix</div>
<div class="artist-role">Guitar · Wah &amp; Fuzz</div>
<div class="artist-desc">Pioneered the wah pedal as melodic voice; used controlled feedback as structural melody, treating effects as extensions of emotional expression rather than embellishment.</div>
</div>
<div class="artist-card hidden stagger-2">
<div class="artist-name">Brian Eno</div>
<div class="artist-role">Producer · Tape &amp; Ambience</div>
<div class="artist-desc">Invented ambient music via tape loop accidents. Oblique Strategies cards drove process. Processing and delay transformed texture into environment and atmosphere.</div>
</div>
<div class="artist-card hidden stagger-3">
<div class="artist-name">Trent Reznor</div>
<div class="artist-role">NIN · Industrial Distortion</div>
<div class="artist-desc">Weaponized distortion and dynamics as narrative arc. Compression and clipping carry emotional weight in NIN's industrial soundscape; silence shaped as much as noise.</div>
</div>
<div class="artist-card hidden stagger-4">
<div class="artist-name">Daft Punk</div>
<div class="artist-role">Electronic · Filter as Structure</div>
<div class="artist-desc">Made filter sweeps a compositional device — the rising lowpass in "Da Funk" and "Around the World" replaces chord changes. Effects serve architecture, not decoration.</div>
</div>
<div class="artist-card hidden stagger-1">
<div class="artist-name">Burial</div>
<div class="artist-role">UK Garage · Reverb &amp; Texture</div>
<div class="artist-desc">Lo-fi crackle, pitch-shifted vocals, and reverb decay as emotional space. Silence and decay carry as much weight as rhythm; texture over clarity is the aesthetic.</div>
